## DSA, LLD and HLD Questions (Microsoft Interview Prep)

This file organizes your questions into DSA, LLD, and HLD. Detailed, interview-ready solutions live in these files:
- `MS/DSA.md`
- `MS/LLD.md`
- `MS/HLD.md`

### DSA
- Canonical file path simplification (see `MS/DSA.md#canonical-file-path-simplification`)
- LeetCode 1011: Capacity To Ship Packages Within D Days (binary search) (see `MS/DSA.md#capacity-to-ship-packages-within-d-days`)
- Next closest time using only current digits (see `MS/DSA.md#next-closest-time-using-available-digits`)
- Gas Station (optimal O(n)) (see `MS/DSA.md#gas-station`)
- Substring with Concatenation of All Words (sliding window by word-length) (see `MS/DSA.md#substring-with-concatenation-of-all-words`)
- LRU Cache (see `MS/DSA.md#lru-cache`)
- Core templates: BFS/DFS, sliding window, DP on arrays/strings (see `MS/DSA.md#core-templates`)

### LLD
- Alert Monitoring System: sensors, thresholds, alerts, push vs pull models (see `MS/LLD.md#alert-monitoring-system`)
